  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, such AI-enhanced multisensory systems hold therapeutic promise, notably in rehabilitating individuals suffering from sensory disorders or conditions like anosmia and ageusia by gradually retraining and stimulating their sensory pathways.",
    "The convergence of AI, VR, and AR technologies thus represents a transformative frontier, challenging traditional conceptions of taste and aroma perception, and opening novel possibilities for both consumer experiences and medical interventions.",
    "Furthermore, the integration of AI with advancements in materials science shows significant promise for developing more precise and sensitive sensors (Hassan et al. 2023).",
    "For instance, innovative sensors based on nanomaterials exhibit heightened sensitivity and selectivity, allowing for more accurate analysis of complex aroma and flavor components.",
    "As these sensors become more sophisticated, combining them with AI algorithms could revolutionize various applications, including rapid food testing in quality assurance processes, enhancing consumer experiences through personalized product offerings, and even providing tailored nutrition plans based on individual sensory profiles."
